This was tasty and attractive, but I'm not sure I would make it again. The reason I might not is that I generally make a dish like this only at holiday time, and I'm not sure this would be my definitive cranberry side dish. There are others I might prefer, and I probably won't make two. However, we did enjoy it.

Rating: 4
I substituted 1/4 cup of chopped crystallized ginger for the celery. I served this with a sauce of 1/2 cup sour cream, 1/2 cup plain yougurt,a couple T. of brown sugar and 1 T of the crystallized ginger. May add more brown sugar to taste. I never have much luck with hot wet towels and metal molds so I used a hair dryer to warm the mold.

